et, England","Compton-Martyn,Somerset,England.":"Compton Martin, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Roynan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Cormac, Nuala.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Rónáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Rónán</i>’, a personal name apparently based on a diminutive of <i>rón</i> ‘seal’."],"variants":[{"name":"Ronayne","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan.","Irish (Waterford and Cork): from <b>Ó Rónáin</b>, see   Ronan  ."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":12,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":37,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":50,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The Firs